  "issue_title": "[bug] agent: 4096-token harness checks exist but are never run at genie-core boot",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nOn `main`, `genie_core::agent_harness::validate_limited_context_agent()` enforces the Jetson 4096-token prompt/tool/memory budget, but it is only called from unit tests \u2014 `genie-core` boot assembles the live system prompt and logs `system_prompt_sha` without running the harness, so oversized configs ship silently.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. On an x86_64 Linux dev host:\n   ```bash\n   cd genie-claw\n   ```\n2. Confirm the harness API exists:\n   ```bash\n   sed -n '38,105p' crates/genie-core/src/agent_harness.rs\n   ```\n3. Confirm boot path does **not** call it:\n   ```bash\n   grep -n validate_limited_context_agent crates/genie-core/src/main.rs\n   grep -rn validate_limited_context_agent crates/genie-core/src --include='*.rs' | grep -v agent_harness.rs\n   ```\n   **Pass (bug present):** `main.rs` has no matches; only test module references remain.\n4. Compare with boot prompt assembly (SHA logged, no budget check):\n   ```bash\n   sed -n '120,138p' crates/genie-core/src/main.rs\n   ```\n5. Run the existing unit test (proves harness works in isolation):\n   ```bash\n   cargo test -p genie-core compact_agent_contract_passes_4096_token_budget\n   cargo test -p genie-core oversized_memory_hydration_fails_the_harness\n   ```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- At `genie-core` boot (and ideally `/api/health` / `genie-ctl status`), run `validate_limited_context_agent()` against the assembled system prompt, live `tool_defs()`, and a representative memory-hydration sample for the configured `[agent]` profile.\n- Fail or emit a structured `WARN`/`ERROR` when `prompt_tool_memory_budget`, `tool_manifest_budget`, or `memory_hydration_budget` checks fail \u2014 same thresholds documented in `doc/milestone-1-portable-home-agent.md`.\n- M1 deployments should not start with a prompt/tool manifest that already exceeds the 4096-token contract.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\n- Boot logs `system_prompt_sha` and prompt byte length but never evaluates harness checks.\n- A config or memory growth that breaks the 4096-token budget is only caught if someone runs the isolated unit tests manually.\n- Jetson operators can hit context overflow / degraded tool-call accuracy with no boot-time signal.\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### JetPack / L4T version\n\n_No response_\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\nv1.0.0-alpha.10 / `main`\n\n### Relevant logs\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Additional context\n\n**Suggested files:** `crates/genie-core/src/main.rs`, `crates/genie-core/src/agent_harness.rs`, `crates/genie-core/src/server.rs` ",
